  "informal_statement": "General pigeonhole principle: if s and t are finite sets of naturals with t strictly smaller than s, and f maps every element of s into t, then some two distinct elements of s collide under f.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Directly `Finset.exists_ne_map_eq_of_card_lt_of_maps_to`, the same lemma the concrete `pigeonhole_3_into_2` instance specializes.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem pigeonhole_general (s t : Finset ℕ) (f : ℕ → ℕ) (hc : t.card < s.card) (hf : ∀ a ∈ s, f a ∈ t) : ∃ x ∈ s, ∃ y ∈ s, x ≠ y ∧ f x = f y",
